         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Hobart ¶ 2nd March 1882 ¶ Dear Baron von Mueller ¶  ¶ I have been asked for the name of the enclosed, which is becoming a troublesome weed on the North Coast. Perhaps you will kindly identify it. ¶  ¶...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.03.02</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Thomas Stephens</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M57, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Hobart</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">2nd March 1882</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have been asked for the name of the enclosed, which is becoming a troublesome weed on the North Coast. Perhaps you will kindly identify it.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Travelling lately near Port Sorrell<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Tas. MS is accompanied with a small note by Stephens: 'Port Sorrell (Trap hills covered with drift sand)'.</p>
               </note> I was struck with the apparently distinctive character of a dwarf Eucalyptus which grows near the Coast. It never seems to grow more than 6 ft or 8 ft high, though the common "Peppermint" which it resembles is found in the same neighbourhood of the usual size. I suppose you will only call it a variety, but if it has a name I should like to know it.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>These specimens are not fit to send, having been carried in my pocket through a long and hot day's ride, but I have none better.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If you wish to make any remarks about the <name key="Cyathea">Cyathea</name> which I obtained from D'Entrecasteaux Channel in November last,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See W. Dobson to M, 4 December 1881.</p>
               </note> I shall be happy to communicate them to the Royal Society next month, when the first meeting of the season is held.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M appears not to have taken up this invitation.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>very truly yrs</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>T. Stephens</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">E. Risdoni</hi>
               </seg>?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">from Mt. Dromedary<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Tas.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Note —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Specimens obtained from a sapling, no adult tree accessible — general habit of tree more like Huon Road tree than those at Risdon.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">T.S.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Postscript is on a separate scrap of paper attached to the letter, annotated by J. H.<seg style=""> </seg>Willis: 'Taken from folder of Euc. tasmanica'. It may not belong with the letter.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cyathea">Cyathea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">Eucalyptus<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline"> Risdoni</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
